Come innovate and solve technology challenges that positively impact the world for one of the largest semiconductor companies in the world! The Data Platforms Group (DPG) college graduate rotation program is an immersive experience for emerging college professions looking join the tech industry workforce to build their business acumen and technical skill while learning about Intel's Data Platforms Group business. 
 
About the Data Platforms Group 
The Data Platforms Group (DPG) is at the heart of Intel's transformation from a PC company to a company that powers the cloud and billions of smart, connected computing-devices. The data center is the hub for every data-driven service - from artificial intelligence to 5G to high-performance computing that fuels the cloud, communication, enterprise, and governments around the world. 
 
About this role 
College graduates hired full-time into this program will complete (3) 7-month rotations prior to final placement within DPG. Rotation professionals will work alongside a combination of DPGs world-class teams gaining exposure to DPG's product portfolio and business processes. 
Rotation assignments will range from working on customer centric solutions, smart connected devices at the edge, silicon development, 5G and data center connectivity, strategy, marketing, business planning and more. Internship focus will vary in nature from software, hardware, and business. 
 
In this role you will work on challenging technical and business projects that help drive critical business and organizational goals 
Learn about Intel's Data Centric products and business 
Build a robust technical and business acumen 
Attend intern exclusive events that provide countless professional development and networking opportunities 
Receive coaching and mentoring from our internal network of professionals 
 
The candidate should exhibit the following behavioral traits: 
Effectively balance technical skills with relationship-building capabilities 
Drive for results, a passion to win, the desire to collaborate and ability to build strong, influential relationships 
Communication skills (oral and written) 
Qualifications 
Minimum Requirements: 
Currently enrolled in and pursuing a BS,MS,PhD program and studying electrical engineering, computer engineering, computer science or a business-related field 
6 plus months experience in: 
Programming experience in any of the following: VHDL, Verilog, C/C++, Perl, Python, TCL, Linux, Bash 
Technical experience in any of the following: digital Logic, digital circuit design, Makefile and networking domains, kernel OS subsystems, communication protocols: TCP,IPv4/6,IPSec,Ethernet, kernel drivers, artificial, deep, and machine learning, source- 
Inside this Business Group 
The Data Center Group (DCG) is at the heart of Intel’s transformation from a PC company to a company that runs the cloud and billions of smart, connected computing devices. The data center is the underpinning for every data-driven service, from artificial intelligence to 5G to high-performance computing, and DCG delivers the products and technologies—spanning software, processors, storage, I/O, and networking solutions—that fuel cloud, communications, enterprise, and government data centers around the world. 
Other Locations 
US, California, Santa Clara; US, Arizona, Phoenix; 
 
 
